![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/05da5756-5313-4580-b172-d0cb282e5ea5/218.jpg)

1997 was a weird year for comic book films. During that year two trailblazing comic book films were released, highlighting black protagonists. The problem was...they weren't very good. Now that diversity is stronger than ever in comic book media, it is time to look back at these pioneer films and pit them together to debate Which WAS Worse! Join us in this spirited debate that has become a staple of the Major Issues Podcast!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
